cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with person retrieval and appearance variations in images. It also involves the use of deep neural networks for image processing, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of masks and fine-grained information suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed ranking loss function and the focus on mitigating interference from similar negative samples suggest that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Lastly, the potential security implications of person retrieval suggest that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
